  "prompt": "Which is the best college in India for doing mech engineering except for the IITs?",
  "response": "If you're looking for the best colleges in India for Mechanical Engineering outside of the IITs, here are some highly reputed institutions:\n\n### **National Institutes of Technology (NITs):**\n1. **NIT Trichy (National Institute of Technology, Tiruchirappalli)**\n2. **NIT Surathkal (National Institute of Technology Karnataka, Surathkal)**\n3. **NIT Warangal (National Institute of Technology, Warangal)**\n4. **NIT Calicut (National Institute of Technology, Calicut)**\n\n### **Birla Institute of Technology and Science (BITS):**\n1. **BITS Pilani (Pilani Campus)**\n2. **BITS Goa**\n3. **BITS Hyderabad**\n\n### **Indian Institutes of Information Technology (IIITs):**\nWhile IIITs are primarily focused on IT, some of them offer interdisciplinary programs in Mechanical Engineering.\n\n### **Delhi Technological University (DTU)**\n- Formerly Delhi College of Engineering (DCE), it is one of the top engineering colleges in India.\n\n### **Jadavpur University (JU), Kolkata**\n- Known for its strong engineering programs, especially in Mechanical Engineering.\n\n### **Vellore Institute of Technology (VIT), Vellore**\n- Offers a robust Mechanical Engineering program with modern facilities.\n\n### **SRM Institute of Science and Technology, Chennai**\n- Known for its engineering programs and state-of-the-art infrastructure.\n\n### **Manipal Institute of Technology (MIT), Manipal**\n- Offers a well-rounded Mechanical Engineering program with excellent placement opportunities.\n\n### **College of Engineering, Pune (COEP)**\n- One of the oldest and most reputed engineering colleges in India.\n\n### **PES University, Bangalore**\n- Known for its strong academic curriculum and placement records in engineering.\n\n### **Thapar Institute of Engineering and Technology, Patiala**\n- Offers a comprehensive Mechanical Engineering program with good industry connections.\n\n### **PSG College of Technology, Coimbatore**\n- Known for its strong focus on practical engineering education and research.\n\n### **Institute of Chemical Technology (ICT), Mumbai**\n- While primarily focused on chemical engineering, it also offers programs in Mechanical Engineering.\n\n### **Symbiosis Institute of Technology (SIT), Pune**\n- Offers a modern curriculum in Mechanical Engineering with a focus on innovation.\n\n### **Amrita Vishwa Vidyapeetham, Coimbatore**\n- Known for its interdisciplinary approach and strong research focus.\n\nThese institutions are highly regarded for their academic rigor, research opportunities, and placement records in Mechanical Engineering. Choosing the best college depends on your specific preferences, such as location, campus facilities, and career goals.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
